-- APPENDIX: Non-retraction of f  (tex lines 599–616)
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- The tex also proves that f has no retraction r : B∞×B∞ → B∞.
-- This shows the surjection s : N∞ + N∞ → N∞ has no section.
--
-- Proof sketch:
--   If r is a retraction of f, then r(0,gₖ) = g_{2k+1} and r(gₖ,0) = g_{2k}.
--   So r(0,1) ≥ r(0,gₖ) = g_{2k+1} for all k.
--   Therefore r(0,1) = ⋀_{i∈I} ¬gᵢ for some finite I.
--   Similarly r(1,0) = ⋀_{j∈J} ¬gⱼ for some finite J.
--   But r(0,1) ∧ r(1,0) = r((0,1)·(1,0)) = r(0,0) = 0,
--   which contradicts finMeetNeg∞ being always nonzero.
--
-- This is not yet formalized.
